-- Munger Gives $18.9 Million in Berkshire Shares to University
-- B y   D a n   R e i c h l
-- 2012-03-02T19:48:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-02/munger-gives-18-9-million-in-berkshire-shares-to-university.html
Charles Munger, the billionaire vice
chairman of  Berkshire Hathaway Inc. (BRK/A) , donated Class A shares
valued at about $18.9 million to the  University of Michigan .  Munger, 88, donated 158 shares on Feb. 21, according to a
filing today to the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dan Reichl in  San Francisco  at 
 dreichl@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
